editorialNotes.standard: Peacock TV is for serious TV fans. It has plenty of familiar titles: The Office, 30 Rock, Parks and Recreation, Saturday Night Live, Downton Abbey, Two and a Half Men, Yellowstone, The King of Queens, and Law & Order: SVU, to name a few. Youll also find new episodes of The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon and kids shows like Curious George, as well as live coverage of Premier League soccer. Looking for wrestling? Peacock is now the home of the WWEs new events and its giant streaming library.

editorialNotes.standard: If you ever see a group of teenagers (or twenty- or thirtysomethings) filming themselves doing literally anything, know this: Theyre probably making a video to share on TikTok. Its infinite scroll of new videos combines perfectly edited lip-synching, hilarious sketches, and mesmerizing dance moves with delightful special effects and filters. Its hard not to fall in love with everyones fluffy pets, awkward parents, impressive glow-ups, fails of every kind, and songs and pop-culture references that spark a million memes.
editorialNotes.short: Make awesome short music videos that you can share with the world.

editorialNotes.standard: There are a hundred different ways to share things with your friends, but Discord stands out as a particularly good one. You can create individual groups (called servers) for your friends: the group that you play videogames with, the group that goes to the cinema together, and so on. This app first made its name among videogame players, but these days, Discord is used by everyone, in no small part because its easy to understand, quick to set up, and slick to use.
editorialNotes.short: A social network for gamers to chat in real time.

editorialNotes.standard: Walmarts app lets you browse thousands of products, search for items that have recently gone on sale and even refill your prescriptions. But the savings catcher is pure genius: scan a receipt for any purchase made in the last seven days, and if a competitor in your area is advertising a lower price, Walmart automatically gives you the difference. Its a fantastic, hassle-free way to save money without the need to shop around.
editorialNotes.short: Shop groceries and millions of other items

editorialNotes.standard: Airbnb has totally changed the way we find places to stay. The unique service is packed with amazing spots all around the worldfrom cottages in France to New York City condos. Book private rooms, share homes with a host, or list your own space. This full-featured app boasts thousands of rent-ready pads, intuitive filters, and a beautiful design.
editorialNotes.short: Book a place to stay for your dream get-away.

editorialNotes.standard: Convinced youve run out of things to watch? Amazon Prime Video may be able to prove otherwise. The app is brimming with brilliant films, dramas, and comedies, as well as sports and childrens TV, all available to watch on demand. We love the ultra-high-quality 4K streaming and the slick UI. Oh, and the ability to create multiple user profiles and download series to watch later. There are also hundreds of Amazon Originals to check outgreat series and films produced by Amazon Studios that you wont find anywhere else.
editorialNotes.short: Prime entertainment whenever you want.

editorialNotes.standard: Before Canva came along, you had to invest in some pretty serious software (and have some pretty serious skills) to create even simple graphics. But with tens of thousands of templates and nearly unlimited ways to customize them, Canva has democratized design. With this easy-to-use app, you can master logos, posters, and invitations in minutes, not months.
editorialNotes.short: Quickly create posts for social media or your small business.

editorialNotes.standard: Whether youre looking for the latest cant-miss dramas, comedies, or reality hits, Max has something for everyone. Watch HBO Original series like Succession, The Last of Us, The White Lotus, and Love & Death. Revisit classics like Friends, South Park, and The Big Bang Theory. And enjoy unscripted treats from Discovery like Fixer Upper, MythBusters, Dr. Pimple Popper, Deadliest Catch, and Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives.

We love that Cash App freed us from personal checks and IOUs. But we get really excited about Boosts: instant discounts when using your Cash Card. No matter if you swipe your physical Cash Card or tap to pay with Apple Pay, Boosts give you coupon-like perks just for spending money at restaurants, coffee shops, and popular stores.
editorialNotes.short: Easily buy stocks and crypto, track their performance, and cash out in this trusted app.

editorialNotes.standard: From its humble origin as a fun way to send self-erasing photo messages, Snapchat has grown into one of our favorite social media apps. And not just for the hilarious face filters and cool geographical photo tags. Its become one of the best ways to share memories, maintain friendships, and stay up to date on news and views from our go-to websites.

editorialNotes.standard: Fans of critically acclaimed CBS series like The Good Fight, NCIS, The Stand, and The Late Show With Stephen Colbert will love Paramount+. Sports fans can stream the NCAA tournament, the UEFA Champions League, the NFL on CBS, and the Masters. Newshounds can tune in to 60 Minutes and CBS Evening News. Star Trek series past, present, and future are establishing their home base here too. And theres loads to watch with kids, including Dora the Explorer, Paw Patrol, Blues Clues, and the best of Nickelodeons streaming catalog.

People power meets the open road in this amazing navigation app. Wazes crowd-sourced alerts come from real drivers, not algorithms, delivering info you wont see anywhere else to keep your commute flowing. The friendly interface and convenient detour routing really help the app shine, and its social-network integration make road trips with buddies a blast.
editorialNotes.short: Find the best way.

editorialNotes.standard: With its friendly approach and awesome updates, Duolingos long been one of our favorite apps for learning another language. Its secret: making the process genuinely fun. Engaging mini-games test your reading, writing, and speaking skills, and joining a club (where you can encourage and compete with others) adds a great social element. Bonus: all those languages and games are available for free!
editorialNotes.short: Learn a new language. Join a club, chat with bots, and get reminders to practice.
